                "abstract": "This is an exclusive interview with Ed Osborn who is currently a sound artist in Oakland and was the director of SoundCulture\u201996. This interview tackles Ed's contribution to the event which took place all over the Bay Area. Many of Ed\u2019s practices include Installations, Acoustic, Ecology Sound, Sound Vibration, and Audio Signals. The interview provides a behind the scenes look at how SoundCulture\u201996\u2019s came together, its impact on the region, and reflections on Obsborn\u2019s artistic practice. Many of his sound practices help garner the audience\u2019s attention by holding sound festival events all over the world which has helped Ed gain recognition as well as building up his sound projects portfolio. ",
