                "authors": "Jenny Hager",
                "authorUrl": "https://jennykhager.com/bio/",
                "abstract": "In the article, the author delves into the shifting landscape of technology and art in response to recent world events. The article notes the presence and reliability of low-tech solutions in times of crisis, using the post-9/11 era as a historical example. The article also explores the influence of the \u201c.com'' bubble burst in reshaping societal perspectives and attitudes towards technology. She examines the transition from a technology-dominated culture to one that emphasizes content and low-tech/high-concept approaches in various fields, including security, business, marketing, and art. The article reflects on the importance of physical experiences and human interaction within a technologically saturated world.",
