                "authors": "Pierre L\u00e9vy",
                "authorUrl": "https://pierrelevyblog.com/ ",
                "abstract": "Description of Pierre Levy\u2019s research project on the measurement and progression of collective intelligence. The article is divided into several sections: Theoretical Research, Theory of collective intelligence, Design and conception of a software implementing the theory, Principles of cartography of collective Intelligence, and Empirical Research. Specifics about the  project at the Canada Research Chair in Collective Intelligence at the University of Ottawa are detailed. The project aims to create a new research field which studies the \"cognitive power\" of groups. \"Cognitive power\" is defined as a power that utilized new communication techniques for intellectual collaboration as well as the intentional improvement of cultural and social factors. In Theoretical Research the author defines factors which he aims to use to define collective intelligence. The software, \"The collective Intelligence Game,\" is used for collaboration, institutional representation, data visualizations, and as a learning game. The next section details the other aims of the author's research, unrelated to developing his theoretical model and software. The article closes with a description of how research will proceed in the following years.",
