                "abstract": "The article \"The Collective Intelligence Game: A Project about Collective Learning and Understanding\u201d focuses on the studying of collective intelligence on how it is like an ecosystem, built upon a group of people sharing their knowledge and wisdom freely together. Its framework concept isn\u2019t limited to being between in-person, going even globally, crossing out the cultural boundaries for as long as one has similar knowledge to collaborate between. Yet it is still in the works and the best framework for collective intelligence to be working can take the form as a \u201cgame\u201d to data-process the feed information.",
