                "abstract": "An overview of Ars Virtua, a virtual art center and gallery situated in the online platform Second Life. The article explains that Ars Virtua was created to showcase new types of artwork in virtual spaces, such as virtual sculpture and architecture. The article mentions the location of Ars Virtua within Second Life and its building structure. Ars Virtua aims to bridge the gap between the 3D virtual world and reality, exploring the possibilities of virtual space as a new form of reality. The article also outlines the mission of Ars Virtua, which includes promoting the development of a virtual commons for idea exchange, stimulating economic interest in virtual work, and providing a platform for transvergence with other media fields. Additionally, the article mentions programs like the artist-in-residence initiative and the hosting of a New Media Conference. It concludes by providing information about Second Life and how users can join this virtual world.",
