                "title": "Executable: Pacific Rim Visual Directory",
                "url": "http://switch.sjsu.edu/archive/mambo/switch_21/pacific_rim_visual_directory.html",
                "authors": "Aaron Siegel",
                "authorUrl": "https://www.datadreamer.com/about",
                "abstract": "This article describes the Pacific Rim Visual Directory, which serves multiple purposes in the new media arts community: it helps analyze trends in creative interests within the Pacific Rim region, acts as a social networking tool, connecting individuals with similar artistic interests, and serves as a platform for emerging collaborations and organizations. The directory visually represents relationships between artists through colored lines: yellow for shared interests, orange for shared organization affiliation, and red for collaborations. Clicking on a red dot allows exploration of a short artist profile.",
